TC_BOOKS_001 – Retrieve list of books

Description:
  Verify that the API returns a valid list of books

Request:
GET /books

Expected result:

  Status code: 200
  Response time < 500ms
  Response is an array
  Array is not empty
  Each object contains:
	id
    name
    type
    available

Actual Result:

All conditions satisfied. Response returned valid book list.

Status: Pass


TC_BOOKS_002 - Validate limit parameter (invalid values)

Case: limit = 0
Request: GET /books?limit=0

Expected result:

	Status code: 400
	Error message for invalid input

Actual Result:

Status code: 400 Bad Request

{
    "error": "Invalid value for query parameter 'limit'. Must be greater than 0."
}

Status: Pass

Case: limit = negative value
Request: GET /books?limit=-1

Expected result:

Status code: 400
Error message for invalid input

Actual Result:

Status code: 400 Bad Request

{
    "error": "Invalid value for query parameter 'limit'. Must be greater than 0."
}

Status: Pass

TC_BOOKS_003 - Validate type parameter (invalid value)

Request: GET /books?type=none

Expected result:

Status code: 400
Error message for invalid input, listing valid values

Actual Result:

Status code: 400 Bad Request

{
    "error": "Invalid value for query parameter 'type'. Must be one of: fiction, non-fiction."
}

Status: Pass






Test scripts (Postman):
pm.test("Status code is 200", function () {
    pm.response.to.have.status(200);
});

pm.test("Response time is less than 500ms", function () {
    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(500);
});

let jsonData = pm.response.json();

pm.test("Status is OK", function () {
    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.eql("OK");
});
